1. The Reality Check

What This Upgrade Is NOT

❌ Not Doing ✅ Actually Doing
Replacing the main SoC Adding firmware to existing MCU
Adding new hardware Using existing ARM Cortex-M/RISC-V core
Building a new NPU Repurposing the always-on coprocessor
Replacing Android/iOS Adding a background service

The upgrade is 90% firmware, 10% system integration.

Why This Works

ST-T1024 is designed to run on existing 32-bit microcontrollers (ARM Cortex-M, RISC-V RV32) with:

· ≥ 100 MHz clock speed
· ≥ 1 MB SRAM
· ≥ 3 MB ROM/Flash
· Power gating support (<5 ns wake)

Your smartphone already has this hardware.

