7. The 3-Year Evolution Cycle

How It Works on a Smartphone

Year Activity Responsibility
Year 1 Deploy ST-T1024 with initial tiles (20+ domains) Firmware team
Year 2 Collect anonymized query logs Sensor Hub + App
Year 3 Unsupervised clustering → Refine tiles Cloud-based offline processing
Year 3+ Push updated ROM/SRAM via OTA update Sovereign update (SK-1024)

The OTA Update Flow

```
Smartphone → Collects anonymized queries (3 years)
    ↓
Uploads to manufacturer's secure server
    ↓
Unsupervised learning → New tile boundaries
    ↓
Encrypted update packet (SK-1024 protocol)
    ↓
OTA update → 25% SRAM updated (ROM stays immutable)
    ↓
New tiles active for next 3 years
    ↓
Repeat every 3 years
```

Tile Discovery Process

```
2-3 trillion aggregated, anonymized user queries
    ↓
Unsupervised deterministic topological clustering
